text: Abdoul Khadre Mbaye Niane (born 20 August 1988) is a Senegalese swimmer. He competed in the men's 50 metre freestyle event at the 2016 Summer Olympics. ==Major results== ===Individual=== ====Long course==== {| |- !bgcolor="#eeeeee" colspan="6"|Representing |- |rowspan=2|2008 |rowspan=2|African Championships |rowspan=2 align=left | Johannesburg, South Africa |6th |100 m freestyle |55.28 |- |7th |200 m freestyle |2:08.07 |- |rowspan=5|2016 |Olympic Games |align=left | Rio de Janeiro, Brazil |48th (h) |50 m freestyle |23.66 |- |rowspan=4|African Championships |rowspan=4 align=left | Bloemfontein, South Africa |4th |50 m freestyle |23.44 |- |7th |100 m freestyle |52.70 |- |9th (h) |200 m freestyle |2:02.03 |- |4th |50 m breaststroke |29.55 |} ===Relay=== ====Long course==== {| |- !bgcolor="#eeeeee" colspan="6"|Representing |- |2008 |African Championships |align=left | Johannesburg, South Africa |bgcolor="cc9966"|3rd |4 x 100 m freestyle |3:42.24 |- |rowspan=3|2016 |rowspan=3|African Championships |rowspan=3 align=left | Bloemfontein, South Africa |bgcolor="cc9966"|3rd |4 x 100 m freestyle |3:39.50 |- |4th |4 x 200 m freestyle |8:26.43 |- |4th |4 x 100 m medley |4:08.56 |} ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1988 births Category:Living people Category:Senegalese male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Senegal Category:Swimmers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Competitors at the 2011 All-Africa Games Category:Competitors at the 2015 African Games Category:Competitors at the 2019 African Games
